    <h1>Navigating the Editor</h1>

    <p>
      The editor has two main areas. The <b>sidebar</b> (1) and the <b>workspace</b> (2).
    </p>

    <p class="img-wrap"><amp-img layout="intrinsic" width="535" height="300" src="./img/docs/getting-started/workspace.png"></amp-img></p>

    <h2 id="Sidebar">Sidebar</h2>

    <p>
      The sidebar is structured into three panels:
    </p>

    <ol>
      <li>
        <b>Insert</b><br/>
        Add images, videos, text and stickers to your story pages, and create page templates.
      </li>
      <li>
        <b>Style</b><br/>
        Modify existing elements on the workspace by tweaking colors or adding links.
        Modify properties related to the currently selected element or group of elements, such as position, size, font properties and more.
        <br>
      </li>
      <li>
        <b>Document</b><br/>
        Control how your story gets published, add any important metadata, and control whether pages auto-advance or need to be tapped manually.
      </li>
    </ol>

    <h2 id="Workspace">Workspace</h2>

    <p>
      In the workspace area you can change your story's title, add and remove story pages, or organize them by changing their order or viewing them in grid mode.
      Design your page by placing and layering assets &amp; elements, view keyboard shortcuts, explore the help center, or go through the checklist for tips on how to improve your story.
    </p>

    <h3 id="Layers">Layers</h3>

    <p>Change the order of elements/layers via the Layer Panel at the bottom corner of the workspace.</p>

    <h2 id="Help-Center">Help Center</h2>

    <p>The help center built into the editor helps you discover tips & resources to help you get the most out of your Web Stories. Access it via the help button at the bottom:</p>

    <p class="img-wrap"><amp-img layout="intrinsic" width="472" height="742" src="./img/docs/getting-started/quick-tips.png"></amp-img></p>

    <h2 id="Checklist">Checklist</h2>

    <p>
      The checklist alerts you about critical issues that may make your story ineligible to appear on platforms such as Google Search and Google Discover. It offers recommendations about common accessibility shortcomings like low contrast and more.
    </p>

    <p class="img-wrap"><amp-img layout="intrinsic" width="401" height="815" src="./img/docs/getting-started/checklist.png"></amp-img></p>

